{"serial": "33021", "department_serial": 29, "code": "ME2073", "class": "B", "name": {"en": "Thermodynamics I", "ch": "熱力學(I)"}, "notice": {"en": "", "ch": ""}, "instructor": {"en": ["Chen,Chen-Yu"], "ch": ["陳震宇"]}, "credits": 3, "time_loc": [{"time": {"week": 1, "session": ["2", "3"]}, "loc": {"building": "E2", "room": "221"}}, {"time": {"week": 4, "session": ["2"]}, "loc": {"building": "E2", "room": "221"}}], "isRequired": true, "isFullSem": false, "MaxStu": 70, "department": {"ch": "機械工程學系", "en": "Department of Mechanical Engineering"}, "system": {"ch": "學士班", "en": "Undergraduate Programme"}, "language": {"ch": "英語", "en": "English"}, "card": {"ch": "部份使用", "en": "Optional"}, "assigned": 52, "selected": 0, "remark": {"ch": "", "en": ""}, "goal": {"ch": "熱為能量作用的一種方式，這門課旨在瞭解物理學上的熱現象，進而探討不同形式的能量之間的轉換，因此是能源科技的基礎課程。本課程也將介紹應用熱力學的工程實例。學生預期能學習到以下能力︰\n1. 從圖表或狀態方程式決定真實物質的性質，例如水蒸氣、冷媒和理想氣體。\n2. 分析在封閉和開放系統中涉及不同工作流體的過程，來決定過程變化關係；和應用熱力學第一定律作能量平衡，來求解熱和功的變化率。\n3. 應用熱力學第二定律分析熱力系統和控制體積系統。", "en": "Thermal energy is a major energy form. This course aims to teach students thermal phenomena in physics and explore the conversion between different forms of energy. Therefore, it is a basic course in energy technology. This course also introduces engineering examples of applied thermodynamics. Students are expected to learn the following abilities:\n1. Determine the properties of real substances such as water vapor, refrigerants, and ideal gases from diagrams or equations of state.\n2. Analyze processes involving different working fluids in closed and open systems to determine process change relationships; and apply the first law of thermodynamics to energy balance to solve for the rates of change of heat and work.\n3. Applying the second law of thermodynamics to analyze thermodynamic systems and control volume systems."}, "outline": {"ch": "1. 熱力學簡介與基本概念\n2. 能量、能量分析與熱力學第一定律\n3. 純物質之性質\n4. 封閉系統的能量分析\n5. 控制體積之質量與能量分析\n6. 熱力學第二定律\n7. 熵", "en": "1. Introduction to basic concepts of thermodynamics\n2. Energy, energy analysis and the first law of thermodynamics\n3. Properties of pure substance\n4. Energy analysis of closed systems\n5. Mass and energy analysis of control volume systems\n6. Second law of thermodynamics\n7. Entropy"}, "textbook": {"ch": "教科書：\nCengel, Y. A. and Boles, M. A., Kanoglu, M. (2023) Thermodynamics: An Engineering Approach, 10th edition, McGraw-Hill, ISBN：9781266152115 東華圖書公司代理，電話：（02）2311-4027 (林文隆0932922193) 。\n\n參考書:\n1. Moran and Shapiro, Fundamentals of Engineering Thermodynamics, 5th Ed., Wiley, 2003.\n2. Sonntag, Borgnakke, and Van Wylen, Fundamentals of Thermodynamics, Wiley, 1998.“", "en": "Textbook：\nCengel, Y. A. and Boles, M. A., Kanoglu, M. (2023) Thermodynamics: An Engineering Approach, 10th edition, McGraw-Hill, ISBN：9781266152115 東華圖書公司代理，電話：（02）2311-4027 (林文隆0932922193) 。\n\nReference:\n1. Moran and Shapiro, Fundamentals of Engineering Thermodynamics, 5th Ed., Wiley, 2003.\n2. Sonntag, Borgnakke, and Van Wylen, Fundamentals of Thermodynamics, Wiley, 1998.“"}, "selfCompiledRate": {"ch": "30", "en": "30"}, "instructMethod": {"ch": "講授\n\n\n\n其他", "en": ["Lecture", "", "", "", "Others"]}, "gradMethod": {"ch": "1. 期中考(2次) :                  20+20 ％\n2. 期末考                            30 ％\n3. 作業＆小考                      20 ％\n4. Classroom participation 10 ％", "en": "1. Midterm (2 midterms) :   20+20 ％\n2. Final Exam                     30 ％\n3. Assignments ＆ Quizs      20 ％\n4. Classroom participation  10 ％"}, "officeHour": {"ch": "Mon.11:00-12:00", "en": "Mon.11:00-12:00"}, "teachWeeks": {"ch": "16+2", "en": "16+2"}, "flexDiscription": {"ch": "自主學習 (助教諮詢)", "en": "self-learning (TA consultation)"}, "domain": {"ch": "基礎學科", "en": "基礎學科"}, "map": {"ch": [{"competencies": "專業知識與技能", "rating": "(5)非常高", "assesments": ["紙筆測驗/會考", "作業練習", "出席/課堂表現"]}, {"competencies": "實驗規劃與資料分析", "rating": "(2)低", "assesments": ["紙筆測驗/會考", "作業練習", "出席/課堂表現"]}, {"competencies": "工程設計與整合", "rating": "(3)普通", "assesments": ["紙筆測驗/會考", "作業練習"